# Snyk (https://snyk.io) policy file
version: v1.25.0
ignore:
  SNYK-CC-TLS-VERIFY:
    - internal/provider/client.go:
        reason: >-
          InsecureSkipVerify is opt-in via the provider's `insecure` config
          flag, intended for users connecting to Poweradmin instances with
          self-signed certificates. The branch only executes when the user
          explicitly sets `insecure = true`. Standard Terraform-provider
          pattern (kubernetes, vault, consul providers do the same).
  'go/HardcodedNonCryptoSecret':
    - internal/provider/client_test.go:
        reason: >-
          Test fixture data for httptest.Server mocks. "secret" is the
          password the mock server checks against in basic-auth tests; it
          never touches a real system.
  'CWE-295':
    - internal/provider/client.go:
        reason: >-
          See SNYK-CC-TLS-VERIFY — user-opt-in insecure flag for self-signed
          certificate endpoints.
  'CWE-798':
    - internal/provider/client_test.go:
        reason: See go/HardcodedNonCryptoSecret — test fixtures only.
  # Findings in tools/go.mod — dev tools (copywrite, terraform-plugin-docs)
  # invoked by `make generate`. They never ship in the provider binary and
  # are not present at runtime. The upstream chains (copywrite →
  # ghinstallation → golang-jwt v4) cannot be moved off v4 until upstream
  # migrates; msgpack v5.3.5 is a go.sum graph reference from terraform-json
  # and go-cty, not actually compiled into the tools build.
  'CWE-405':
    - '*':
        reason: >-
          golang-jwt/jwt v4.5.2 (latest v4) via bradleyfalzon/ghinstallation
          via hashicorp/copywrite. Dev-only dependency for copyright header
          generation; not in the provider binary. ghinstallation has not
          migrated to jwt v5.
  'CWE-209':
    - '*':
        reason: >-
          bradleyfalzon/ghinstallation v2.18.0 (latest) via copywrite.
          Dev-only, not in the provider binary.
  'CWE-1118':
    - '*':
        reason: >-
          Documentation-quality finding on golang-jwt/jwt v4 and
          bradleyfalzon/ghinstallation. Dev-only deps, not in the provider
          binary, and CVSS 2.3 is informational.
  'CWE-1287':
    - '*':
        reason: >-
          vmihailenco/msgpack v5.3.5 appears in tools/ go.sum as a graph
          reference from terraform-json and zclconf/go-cty but is not
          compiled into the tools build (`go mod why` reports it unused).
          Main module already pins msgpack v5.4.1.
